description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to fill a vacancy within the phlebotomy team managed by the Blood Sciences Department at Withybush General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have one part time permanent post (20 hours per week). The successful candidate will work as part of a team to provide a blood sample collection service to the wards and for patient&#39;s attending clinics within the Pathology Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous phlebotomy experience is essential along with good communication skills. There will be a requirement to provide cover at weekends and on Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews for this post will be held on 24th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDarren EvansJob titleBlood Sciences Section ManagerEmail addressdarren.evans2@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01437 773271Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anke Meess, 01437 773230 or anke.meess@wales.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
